ENTRY            G4119   20260422   20260528   20260528       G060
SUBENT        G4119001   20260422   20260528   20260528       G060
BIB                 13         26
TITLE      Cross-section of the natNi(gamma,pxn)58Co reaction
           at the bremsstrahlung end-point energy of 35-94 MeV
AUTHOR     (I.S.Timchenko,O.S.Deiev,S.M.Olejnik,S.M.Potin,
           V.A.Kushni,V.V.Mytrochenko,S.A.Perezhogin,A.Herzan)
INSTITUTE  (4UKRKFT,3SLKSLO)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,61,199,2025)
           #doi:10.1140/epja/s10050-025-01666-7
FACILITY   (LINAC,4UKRKFT) LUE-40
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
METHOD     (ACTIV) Induced beta-delayed gamma-activity measured.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) A semiconductor HPGe detector (Canberra)
           was used with resolutions of 0.8 keV and 1.8 keV (FWHM)
           for the energies Eg = 122 keV and 1332 keV. The
           absolute registration efficiency of the detector was
           calibrated with a standard set of gamma-ray sources
           22Na, 60Co, 133Ba, 137Cs, 152Eu and 241Am.
SAMPLE     The targets made of natural nickel with a diameter
           8 mm and mass about of 80 mg.
MONITOR    (42-MO-100(G,N)42-MO-99,,SIG,,BRA)
           The natMo witness-targets were located close to the
           nickel target. For 100Mo were used the percentage
           value of isotope abundance equal to 9.63%.
DECAY-MON  (42-MO-99,65.924HR,DG,739.500,0.122)
ADD-RES    (COMP) Experimental data are compared with theoretical
            predictions calculated with TALYS code.
HISTORY    (20260417C) UkrNDC
ENDBIB              26
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           29
SUBENT        G4119002   20260422   20260528   20260528       G060
BIB                  5         16
REACTION   (28-NI-0(G,X)27-CO-58,,SIG,,BRA)
DECAY-DATA (27-CO-58-G,70.86D,DG,810.76,0.9945)
ADD-RES    Calculated cross sections for Ni60(g,np)Co58 presented
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) A quadratic sum of statistical and systematic
                   errors.
           (ERR-S,1.0,1.5) The statistical error in the observed
                             gamma-activity,
           (ERR-1) exposure time and the electron current - 0.5%,
           (ERR-2) the number of target atoms - 0.2%,
           (ERR-3,2.,3.) radiation detection efficiency - 2-3%,
           (ERR-4) normalization of the experimental data to the
           yield of the monitoring reaction 100Mo(g,n)99Mo - 5%,
           (ERR-5,,1.) contribution of the 811.85 keV transition
           from the 56Ni nucleus to the full absorption peak at
           810.76 keV resulted error of less than 1%.
STATUS     (TABLE,,I.S.Timchenko+,J,EPJ/A,61,199,2025) Tab.2
ENDBIB              16
COMMON               3          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-4
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
0.5        0.2        5.
ENDCOMMON            3
